HEADWORD: Hygroscope
<hw>Hy"gro*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ wet +
<ets>-scope</ets>: cf. F. <ets>hygroscope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument which shows whether there is
more or less moisture in the atmosphere, without indicating its
amount.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hygroscopic</ent>⟦br⟧
